What flower takes its name from the human testicle? Is your husband rantallion? Does your wife sport a merkin? What's a wittol, 
and why were they once drummed out of town while sitting backwards on a horse? Is sacofricosis a crime, a disease or an hors d'oeuvre? Morton roams 
through centuries of etymological lore to explain the origins of the language of love and sex. It is the perfect book for language-lovers and lovers alike.
